  "body": "Hello \r\nI'm re-syncing a full blockchain (trying to run an archive node with complete transactions)\r\nand have some blocks that are in the range of the Account bloat hack, that are taking sometimes hours to process... is it normal?\r\n\r\nsetup:\r\ngeth 1.6.7 \r\non MacOSX\r\nand I run it with:  geth --cache=4096  (I think it handles better than 2048 and 1024)\r\n\r\nsome examples\r\n\r\n**Block 2406465 = 48 minutes**\r\n`INFO [07-28|10:28:09] Imported new chain segment blocks=1 txs=1 mgas=1.490 elapsed=47m42.848s mgasps=0.001 number=2406465 hash=8c23cd…e04569`\r\n\r\n(https://etherscan.io/block/2406465)\r\n\r\n**Block 2406490 = 2 hours!**\r\n`INFO [07-28|12:49:35] Imported new chain segment blocks=1 txs=9 mgas=1.490 elapsed=2h8m42.748s mgasps=0.000 number=2406490 hash=bbe727…bfaa67`\r\n\r\n(https://etherscan.io/block/2406490)\r\n\r\nwhat I don't understand is that **etherscan says that they where mined in just a few seconds**... how is it possible?\r\n\r\n**any ideas on how to improve this speed?**\r\n\r\nSince we know those blocks where for the transaction bloat attack to the network, wouldn't it be possible to \"exclude\" them from the sync or to treat them as a fast sync only for those specific transactions?\r\nthanks\r\n",
